    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nBuilding universal binary for macOS does not work anymore with Cmake 3.28.0. See the discussion in [Matrix](https://matrix.to/#/!cylwlNXSwagQmZSkzs:matrix.org/$8ZHwxpojHVXF7JrEkBjAke_VLLdDPo2Lk-pDD026m3w?via=matrix.org&via=gitter.im&via=envs.net). @dundargoc identified the commit in Cmake which introduces this problem: <https://gitlab.kitware.com/cmake/cmake/-/commit/872daff159d8c7b3bfdabe3918c2832539168c91>\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n- clone the neovim repository\r\n- execute `./.github/scripts/build_universal_macos.sh`\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nSuccessful build. Instead, one gets\r\n\r\n```\r\nninja: error: build.ninja:612: multiple rules generate build/downloads/luajit/ff204d0350575cf710f6f4af982db146cb454e1a.tar.gz\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.9.4 and upwards\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 14.1.2\r\n",
